        "text": "Perfect! ✅ Circuit built successfully.\n\n## Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Pin Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| D2 | Display (seg A) | via R_A (220Ω) |\n| D3 | Display (seg B) | via R_B (220Ω) |\n| D4 | Display (seg C) | via R_C (220Ω) |\n| D5 | Display (seg D) | via R_D (220Ω) |\n| D6 | Display (seg E) | via R_E (220Ω) |\n| D7 | Display (seg F) | via R_F (220Ω) |\n| D8 | Display (seg G) | via R_G (220Ω) |\n| D9 | BTN_INC (a) | Increment button |\n| D10 | BTN_DEC (a) | Decrement button |\n| GND | Display, both buttons (b) | Common ground |\n\n## Sketch Behavior\n\nThe sketch initializes a counter at 0 and displays it on the 7-segment. Each button press increments or decrements the counter with boundary protection:\n- **BTN_INC (D9):** Increases counter (max 9)\n- **BTN_DEC (D10):** Decreases counter (min 0)\n- The `displayNumber()` function maps each digit 0–9 to the correct segment pattern using if/else logic.\n- Debounce delay: 50ms after a press to prevent jitter.\n\n## Power Budget\n\n| Component | Per-Pin Current | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 7 × 220Ω resistors + display | ~13 mA | At ~2V per segment, 7 LEDs = ~14 mA total |\n| Button inputs (D9, D10) | ~0 mA | Pulled HIGH internally |\n| **Total draw** | **~14 mA** | Well within Arduino's 200 mA limit ✓ |\n\nYour 0–9 counter is ready! Press the buttons to increment/decrement."
